@Andrew_Duncan also check this post https://forum.typst.app/t/why-does-my-header-code-no-longer-work-in-typst-0-13/3940/2?u=vmartel08 which has a useful snippet if you want to do it without a package:

```typ
#let current-chapter-title() = context {
  let headings = query(heading.where(level: 1).before(here()))
  if headings == () { panic("At least one heading must be defined.") }
  headings.last().body
}

#set page(footer: current-chapter-title())

= Heading

``` 

Have you found a solution that works for you?
